â— Plane Equation (implicit form of a plane equation)
â—‹ Looks a lot like an implicit equation for a line
â—‹ f(x, y, z) = ax + by + cz + d = 0
â—‹ Parameters of plane= a, b, c, and d
â—‹ Given P, Q, R that are 3D points:
â–  Find a, b, c, d of plane thru these points
â–  A vector going from P to Q = PQ = Q - P
â–  To get a surface normal that is perpendicular to PQ and PR:
â— N = (PQ x PR)/(|PQ x PR|) = (a, b, c)
â— (cross product) ^
â— Surface normal is the direction of maximum change
