- Q() = B1(t)*p1 + B2(t)*p2 + B3(t)*p3 + B4(t)*p4
- B1(t) + B2(t) + B3(t) + B4(t) = 1 by construction
- Bâ€™s are all non-negative when 0 <= t <= 1
- For a line segment:
- L1(t) = 1 - t
- L2(t) = t
-
- L1(t) + L2(t) = (1-t) + t = 1
- The point can be written as Q(t) = L1(t)*p1 + L2(t)*p2
