Generative Neural Networks
â— Generative- means to make something
â—‹ Can generate: text, music, images, video, â€¦
â— Image Generative Networks:
â—‹ Autoencoders*
â—‹ variational autoencoders- VAEâ€™s for short
â—‹ Generative adversarial networks- GANâ€™s
â—‹ Diffusion models (currently best, can follow prompts)*
â–  All of these use CNNâ€™s (convolutional neural networks)
â— CNNâ€™s have an input and an output
â— Images in, images out
â— Convolutional layer:
â—‹ Image â†’ conv. Layer â†’ image
â–  Use multiple of these in a CNN ^
â–  Humans use 3 channels in an image (r g b)
â–  CNNs use many more than 3 channels
â–  What use are these different channels?
â— Channels represent features in an image
â—‹ Presence of a particular color
â—‹ Low-level features: Edge (is there a sharp edge btwn light
and dark), Corner, Arc, Stripes
â—‹ Higher-level features: Wheel, eye, face, cat
â–  convolution(al):
â— Convolution layer calculates a weighted sum of pixel values
â—
â— After weighted sum, a non-linear function is applied
â—‹ â€œActivation functionâ€
â–  ReLU function (rectified linear unit, gives 0 if the
number is negative, gives the number if itâ€™s
positive)
â–  tanh(x)- hyperbolic function
â–  Activation function â†’ allows the network to
perform boolean-like operations (logical or, and,
not)
â–  CNNs first use: image classification
â— Examples: which digit? 0, 1, 2, â€¦, 9 (10 classes)
â— Cat or dog? (Is the image of a cat or a dog (2 classes)
â— Which breed of dog is it? (25 classes)
â— Input (to a CNN): image, output: set of probabilities
â—‹ [0.01, 0.03, 0.21, 0.67, 0.0027, â€¦] â†’ list of 25 numbers,
referring to the different kinds of breed of dog
â—‹ [pug, terrier, poodle, beagle, â€¦ ]
â–  Most likely to be a beagle, since 0.67 is highest
â— There are other layers of a CNN besides just the convolution
â—‹ Down sampling: image (128x128) â†’ down sampling layer
â†’ smaller image (64x64), very often powers of 2
â—‹ With this an convolutions, you can put together a neural
network
â– 
â–  Train to give good results using training pairs
